3.2. The hybrid stress model element (HSM)

In the formulation of the HSM element the classical Kirchhoff thin plate theory is used directly. With the notation used in Section 3.1, y = 0 everywhere in the plate, 6. = - w,. = 8, and By = - w,, = - 8,. The so-called h brid stress functional for plate bending under the Kirchhoff assumptions can 0.46 be e~tablished:~"

