(1) Considering first the case o the concentrated load application, Figures 6 and 7show that the f DKT and HSM elements are very efficient. Note that mesh B is not effective in modelling the clamped plate problem, since all dofs of the comer element vanish. The influence of mesh orientation on the displacements is more severe for the DKT element than for the HSM element. Convergence from above is obtained for the DKT element, whereas monotonic convergence from below is observed for the HSM element. (2) 'Inthe case of uniform loading, monotonic convergence was achieved with the DKTelement s f with both boundary conditions. However, convergence i less rapid in the case o the clamped plate. The solution accuracy could probably be increased by employing a consistent load representation with a cubic polynomial for w. Monotonic convergence is not achieved in the analysis of the clamped plate using the HSM element.

